---
import LoanProductLayout from "@/layouts/LoanProductLayout.astro";
const title = "Invoice Factoring";
const subtitle = "Invoice factoring lets businesses release money tied up in unpaid invoices. Improve cash flow, reduce stress, and apply online with access to multiple lenders.";
---
<LoanProductLayout title={title} subtitle={subtitle} updatedAt="November 2025">
  
  <!-- What is invoice factoring -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-6">What is invoice factoring?</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Invoice factoring is a type of invoice finance. It allows businesses to release funds tied up in unpaid invoices by selling them to a finance company (the "factor"). The provider advances up to 90% of the invoice value immediately and handles credit control and collections.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed">
      This makes it especially useful for businesses that issue invoices with long payment terms or deal with frequent late payments. The factoring provider takes over the management of your sales ledger and chases payments on your behalf.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- How it works -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-6">How invoice factoring works</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-6 mb-8">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">1</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Invoice your customer</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You invoice your customer for goods or services.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">2</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Sell the invoice</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You sell the invoice to the factoring provider.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">3</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Receive advance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You receive an advance, typically 70%–90% of the invoice value.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">4</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Lender collects</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">The lender collects payment directly from your customer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">5</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Receive balance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You receive the remaining amount, minus service fees.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">Invoice factoring example</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-3">
        You invoice a client for €20,000. The lender advances 85% - that's €17,000.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        When the client pays the full €20,000, the lender deducts a 2% fee (€400) and releases the remaining €2,600 to you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Why choose invoice factoring -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Why choose invoice factoring?</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Bridging payment gaps</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Instead of waiting for 30–90 day invoice terms, you can access working capital almost immediately after invoicing a customer.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Covering operational costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Factor invoices to cover wages, bills, or stock purchases without tapping into reserves.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Investing in growth</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Use released funds for marketing, expansion, or hiring - without needing a long-term loan.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Improving supplier relationships</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Pay suppliers on time to protect trading terms and ensure uninterrupted service.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Key benefits -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Key benefits of invoice factoring</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Faster access to working capital</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">No need to chase payments</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Improves cash flow predictability</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Flexible funding linked to sales</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Can grow with your turnover</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Is it right for your business -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Is invoice factoring right for your business?</h2>
    
    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50 mb-6">
      <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">Invoice factoring is usually suitable for:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">B2B businesses that issue invoices with payment terms</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Companies dealing with frequent late payments</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Businesses that want to outsource credit control</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">SMEs that need to bridge payment gaps without taking on additional debt</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <div class="w-5 h-5 rounded bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5">
            <svg class="w-3 h-3 text-lime-900" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/></svg>
          </div>
          <span class="text-neutral-700">Companies with consistent invoice volumes and reliable customers</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
      <p class="text-neutral-700">
        It may not be suitable if you want to maintain complete control over customer relationships, prefer confidential financing, or have very few invoices. Invoice discounting may be a better option if you want to keep the arrangement private from your customers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Invoice factoring vs invoice discounting -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Invoice factoring vs invoice discounting</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-200">
            <th class="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-black">Feature</th>
            <th class="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-black">Invoice Factoring</th>
            <th class="text-left py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-black">Invoice Discounting</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Client notified</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Yes</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">No</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Who chases payment</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">The lender</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">You</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Confidentiality</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Lower</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">High</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-neutral-100">
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Cost</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Typically higher</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Often lower</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Suitable for</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Businesses needing support</td>
            <td class="py-4 px-4 text-neutral-700">Established businesses</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50 mt-6">
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-black">Key difference:</strong> With factoring, the lender manages your sales ledger and collects payments directly from your customers. With discounting, you retain control over customer relationships and collections, but the arrangement is confidential.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- What are the costs -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-6">What are the costs?</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Invoice factoring costs vary by turnover, industry, and risk. They usually include:
    </p>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Service fee</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">A percentage of invoice value (typically 0.5% to 3%) charged for managing your sales ledger and credit control.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Interest on funds advanced</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Interest charged on the advance amount, usually calculated daily or monthly until the invoice is paid.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Setup fees</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">One-time fees for setting up the facility, though some providers waive these.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Minimum volume requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Some providers require a minimum monthly invoice volume or charge fees if volumes drop below agreed levels.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-zinc-50 mt-6">
      <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">
        <strong class="text-black">Tip:</strong> Always ask for a clear breakdown of all fees and compare the total cost across different providers, not just the advance percentage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Which industries can benefit -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Which industries can benefit from invoice factoring?</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Logistics</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Any business that deals with other businesses could benefit from invoice factoring. Given the large amount of invoices logistics companies send, invoice factoring could be of particular value to them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Construction</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Similarly, construction companies often invoice other businesses, sometimes in extremely large amounts and with long payment terms. For this reason, invoice factoring could provide some support.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Healthcare</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Healthcare companies often raise or pay invoices for medical equipment, essential supplies, and patient care. Invoice factoring can help bridge the gap between raising an invoice and getting paid for these companies.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Recruitment</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Recruitment agencies frequently invoice clients for placements with payment terms. Invoice factoring helps manage cash flow while waiting for client payments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Manufacturing</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Manufacturing businesses often have long production cycles and extended payment terms. Invoice factoring provides working capital to cover operational costs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white hover:border-lime-300 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Wholesale</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Wholesale businesses typically operate on thin margins and need cash flow to purchase inventory. Invoice factoring helps maintain stock levels and supplier relationships.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Alternatives -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">Alternatives to invoice factoring</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Invoice discounting</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">You retain client control and collections. Confidential arrangement where you manage your own credit control.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Revolving credit facility</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Reusable funding for cash flow gaps. Draw and repay as needed, only paying interest on what you use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Short-term loan</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Fixed repayment plan for one-off needs. Provides a lump sum with predictable monthly repayments.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Merchant cash advance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Based on future card sales. Flexible repayment model tied to your revenue, ideal for retail and hospitality.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Business overdraft</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Flexible buffer from your bank. Pre-approved credit line for short-term cash flow needs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Asset finance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Helps you buy or lease business equipment. Spread the cost of assets over time while preserving cash flow.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- How Runway works -->
  <div class="mb-16">
    <h2 class="font-heading font-light text-3xl md:text-4xl text-black mb-8">How to apply with Runway</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-6">
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">1</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">No fees for comparing</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">No fees for comparing and no obligation to proceed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">2</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Tell us about your business</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Tell us about your business and the funding you need.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">3</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Compare tailored offers</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Compare tailored offers from multiple lenders.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 bg-white text-center">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-lime-100 flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-4">
          <span class="text-lime-900 font-semibold text-xl">4</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-black mb-2">Provide documents</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 text-sm">Provide documents for underwriting.</p>
      </div>
